title.narrative: STRENGTHENED LOCAL GOVERNANCE

description.narrative: Government and local authorities have strengthened capacities and skills to operationalize key policies and frameworks to address child deprivations and are held accountable for delivering of quality and resilient, child-friendly services., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid), Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid), Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys grow up in resilient, inclusive and child friendly communities, that are supported by enabling environment and systems that provide an equitable chance in life.

description.narrative: UNICEF contributed to thecomprehensive reform of Malawi’s decentralized systems at policy framework level (National Decentralization Policy), analytical level (stock-take of the functioning of fiscal decentralization and mapping of minimum packages of services) and legal framework level (review of the PFM Bill and Local Government Bill). These interventions are part of the most ambitious attempt to sector reform in Malawi and a leading example of how UNICEF can engage in system strengthening.;UNICEF signed MOUs on implementing Child Friendly Communities Initiative with Chikwawa and Nsanje District Councils to implement the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/12/2021
